    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1879-03-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1879-03-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="41" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d41">
                <head>No. 30.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Kasson</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Evarts</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vienna</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1879-03-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 11, 1879</date>.
                            (Received March 27.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 173.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: An official summary of the commercial movement
                        for the year 1878 has been published. It shows a total value of imports of
                        579,547,828 florins, or in round numbers $278,000,000, and a total value of
                        exports of 698,302,513 florins, or in round numbers of $335,000,000, Thus
                        the balance of trade appears to have been in favor of Austria-Hungary by
                        about $57,000,000 for the year 1878.</p>
                <p>The increase of imports over the amount reported for the year 1877 is
                        24,320,780 florins. The increase of exports is 36,270,309 florins.</p>
                <p>These results indicate an amelioration of the financial condition of the
                        empire and of its people.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JOHN A. KASSON.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
